    "description": "<p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Part travel journal, part visual novel with a hint of psychological horror, Melbourne: Route 96 is an experimental game about catching a tram in the wrong direction.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong><i>&quot;If you’re honest with your camera, then a polaroid will never lie. ..&quot;</i></strong></p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Loosely inspired by true events, the game includes snippets of real conversations overheard whilst exploring Melbourne, Australia.</p><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" ><strong>FEATURES</strong></p><ul class=\"bb_ul\"><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Short duration (15 - 20 minutes)</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Hand drawn graphics</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Multi media experience with original photography &amp; videography</p></li><li><p class=\"bb_paragraph\" >Travel journal</p></li></ul>",
